The paper presents a deep reinforcement learning algorithm for continuous control tasks, which involves learning policies for continuous action spaces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with robotics tasks such as legged locomotion and car driving, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions learning policies directly from raw pixel inputs, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with control tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
